Social Media Do's and Don'ts for College Students
Prepared by: Amrita Singh | Reg. No.: 25BCE10970
Course: CSE0001 – Digital Literacy | VIT Bhopal University

Do's
1 Keep your profile photo and bio professional on platforms like LinkedIn and GitHub.
2 Think before you post — ask yourself: "Would I be comfortable if my professor or a future employer saw this?"
3 Use privacy settings to control who can see personal posts on Instagram, Facebook, etc.
4 Credit others when sharing their content, ideas, or creative work.
5 Log out of your accounts on shared or public devices (library computers, labs, friends' phones).

DON'Ts
1 Don't share your location in real time (e.g., "I'm home alone right now" or tagging your exact location).
2 Don't post confidential information — exam question papers, internal college notices, timetables, or faculty communications.
3 Don't engage with or share unverified news, rumours, or viral posts without fact-checking.
4 Don't use social media to harass, bully, criticise, or publicly embarrass peers, faculty, or anyone else. 
5 Don't accept follow or friend requests from unknown accounts, especially those with no mutual connections or minimal profile activity.
